ultural milieu of the nineteenth century, drawing on first-hand accounts of Danube cruising. Describing the story of travelers who interacted, met, and visited the places they stopped, Constantin Ardeleanu creates a transnational history of travel up and down the Danube from Vienna to Constantinople. The pleasures and sometimes the travails of the travelers unfold against a backdrop of technical and economic transformation in the crucial period of modernization.  afunded by Opening the Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aRiver steamerszLower Danube RiverxHistoryy19th century. 0aRomaniansxTravel. 0aTravelerszRomaniaxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 19th Century.2bisacsh  aMoldavia.  aTransportation revolution.  aWallachia.  aquarantines.  asociality.2 aOpening the Futureefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2024z978311079758940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789633867549?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633867549zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633867549/original  a978-3-11-079758-9 Central European University Press eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA